	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I'll probably be unpopular for saying this, but I think they should take away the medding on horse. It didn't make sense to have in the first place. I don't think I can meditate any better riding on a horse than I can standing still. All horseback meditation has done is make casters lazy. They have less feel for how to control their aggro.<br />
<br />
And quite honestly, being in a flock of casters on horseback is freaking annoying. Consider phase 3 of time, those of you who have been there. I don't like being on the horse in the first place but consider it a necessary evil sometimes. You'll very rarely see me using it though, except when I really need to. Yaulp all the way!</font></p>
	
